<DOC><DOCNO> AP890908-0094 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-08-89 1219EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--CrumblingCastle     09-08 0131</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Crumbling Castle,0133</SECOND><HEAD>Medieval Fortress Crumbles at Sound of Voices</HEAD><DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The walls of the medieval castle ofPrimda may have resisted many an invading knight centuries ago, butin the 20th century, they crumble at the sound of a human voice.   In July, debris from the crumbling castle in western Bohemiakilled one boy and injured two. In reporting Friday on the cause ofthe accident, the state news agency CTK said chemical changes causedby polluted rain water have resulted in the castle walls havingvirtually no strength.   ``When a group of young people spoke loudly inside the castle,the vault started trembling and one part of it fell down,'' a teamof experts concluded, according to CTK.   It said the castle had been closed.</TEXT></DOC>